            "answer_text": "During WWII, a U.S. naval destroyer won a battle against a Japanese submarine by throwing potatoes at them. Yes you read that right. The U.S. navy ship accidentally got in close proximity with the Japanese ship, and while the U.S. were still frantically trying to mount all weapons on deck, someone decided to throw potatoes in a panic. The Japanese, stunned by this and thought the potatoes were grenades, began throwing them back to the destroyer, which then resulted in a massive potato fight. But the destroyer immediately acted up and got some distance away from the Japanese ship while the Japanese were still distracted by the \u201cgrenades\u201d. Within a few minutes the U.S. managed to get out the real weapons and successfully sink the enemy ship.  The power of potatoes. ",
